Test project to learn docker and minikube and codespace
    1  docker run hello-world
    2  docker images
    3  docker ps
    4  docker ps -a
    5  mkdir project1 && cd project1
    6  touch Dockerfile
    7  ls -la
    8  touch app.js
    9  docker build -t project1:01 .
   10  ls -la
   11  docker images
   12  docker run -p 4000:80 --name app-run1 project1:01
   13  docker build -t project1:02 .
   14  docker images
   15  docker run -p 6000:80 --name app-run1 -d project1:01
   16  docker rm 359
   17  docker run -p 6000:80 --name app-run1 -d project1:01
   19  docker run -p 8080:80 --name app-run2 -d project1:02
  
  How to use local docker images with Minikube?
  https://stackoverflow.com/questions/42564058/how-to-use-local-docker-images-with-minikube

Set the environment variables with eval $(minikube docker-env)
Build the image with the Docker daemon of Minikube (eg docker build -t my-image .)
Set the image in the pod spec like the build tag (eg my-image)
Set the imagePullPolicy to Never, otherwise Kubernetes will try to download the image.